original: Ingemanson, Manfred Elof, fil. mag., läroverksadjunkt, Karlskrona, f. 2/7/88 i Bräkne-Hoby, Blek. 1., av Sven I. o. Elvira Persson. G. 21 m. Sofie Ven-nersten. Barn: Gösta (adopt.) f. 18, Sven 22, Astrid 25. — Stud:ex. i Växjö 09, fil. kand. i Lund 13, fil. mag. 16, provår 19. Res. t. Tyskl. 24, 30, 38 o. 39. Vik, adj. i Karlskrona 17, vik. lektor i Linköp. s. å., i Ystad s. å., tf. förest, f. Jämshögs’by h. folksk. 18, e. lär. i Borås 20, adj. i modersm. o. hist. m. samh :lära v. Karlskrona h. a. 1. sed. 36.
translated: Ingemanson, Manfred Elof, MA, high school teacher, Karlskrona, b. July 2nd, 1888 in Bräkne-Hoby, Blekinge County, son of Sven I. and Elvira Persson. Married on 1921 to Sofie Vennernsten. Children: Gösta (adopted) b. 1918, Sven b. 1922, Astrid b. 1925. Studied at Växjö for matriculation in 1909, Bachelor of Arts at Lund University in 1913, Master of Arts in 1916, teaching apprenticeship in 1919. Traveled to Germany in 1924, 1930, 1938, and 1939. Substitute teacher in Karlskrona in 1917, substitute lecturer in Linköping the same year, in Ystad the same year, acting superintendent at Jämshögs' village school in 1918, regular teacher in Borås in 1920, high school teacher in Swedish and History with social studies at Karlskrona high school since 1936.
